                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/1412: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-25T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 25, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 25—2:42
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1212. American Consul at Yunnanfu telegraphs that with reference to reported sale
                    of French munitions to Yunnan he understands there is now possibility for
                    American manufacturers provided that they quote without delay prices on the
                    following: 200 machine guns caliber 7.92 with 3,000,000 rounds; 10,000 rifles
                    same caliber with 2,500,000 rounds; 100 anti-aircraft guns caliber 13.2 with
                    1,000,000 rounds; 4 anti-aircraft guns caliber 25 millimeters with 40,000
                    rounds. Reported French terms delivered at Yunnanfu approximately 1,750,000 gold
                    dollars.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
